- Engineers who are not directly involved in test schedules are part of a hierarchy that is built recursively;
- The equipment utilization is tracked by counting the number of schedules each piece of equipment has been involved in;
- Test results include detailed information such as the test type, category, subcategory, status, notes, and the names and qualifications of the engineers.

- 'Thermal' refers to tests related to temperature conditions;
- 'High Temperature Storage' is a subcategory of thermal tests, typically involving storing items at high temperatures for a specified duration;
- 'Temperature Chamber' is a type of equipment used to create and maintain specific temperature conditions for testing purposes.

- Test categories and types are used to classify different kinds of tests;
- The average test duration and temperature are calculated to understand the typical conditions under which tests are conducted;
- The total number of tests provides insight into the frequency of each test type and category.

- 'test category' refers to the type of test such as Thermal or Electrical;
- 'total_test_duration' is the sum of the duration hours for all test conditions within a category;
- 'most time-consuming' refers to the test category with the highest total test duration.
